{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "Caustics",
  "description": "Light through water: a photon-scatter caustics generator. An animated two-octave simplex height field plays the water surface; its gradient bends half a million fresh photons every frame (spawn EveryFrame \u2192 sample the slope \u2192 one Euler step, so the bend amount is literally the water depth), and the photons pile up in a density accumulator exactly where refraction concentrates them \u2014 fold lines brighten because light genuinely converges there, which a scrolling caustics texture can never do. Display follows the FluidSim recipe (VISUAL_PIECES_GRAPH_DRAFTS 'particle-density display recipe'): no display blur, single-texel photons, Extended Reinhard with canvas-area-compensated intensity, white-hot HDR folds on pure black. Depth is the performance card \u2014 bind the sub-bass send and the water gets violent with the low end.",
